Third-party attributions
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Vendor documentation snapshots (gateways/<vendor>/<model>/reference/)
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Each gateway profile is authored from the vendor's own product documentation
(admin URLs, default credentials, config-file paths, chipset, packet-forwarder
mechanism). A snapshot of the documentation page a profile was authored from is
retained under gateways/<vendor>/<model>/reference/ for authoring reference and
drift detection, with its sha256 and retrieval date recorded in the profile's
`provenance` block in gateway.json. These snapshots remain the property of their
respective vendors, are copied for reference only, and are EXCLUDED from the
published npm tarball (see the "files" allowlist in package.json).

The authored artifacts that DO ship — the packet-forwarder config templates
(gateways/<vendor>/<model>/config/*.tmpl.*), the walkthroughs, and the region
channel-plan manifests — are ORIGINAL works created for this project from those
facts, not copied from vendor config dumps. Wire-format and configuration facts
(frequencies, ports, file paths, field names of the Semtech UDP and Basics
Station formats) are not copyrightable; the templates that embed them are
original work under AGPL-3.0-or-later.

LoRa Alliance — RP002 Regional Parameters
-----------------------------------------
The channel-plan values in definitions/regions/*.json (band identifiers,
uplink/RX2 frequencies, sub-band conventions) are facts drawn from the LoRa
Alliance RP002 Regional Parameters specification. These are factual data, not a
copyrightable expression, and are reproduced here for interoperability.
